A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 3 of Chapter 3 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to other state symbols, so as to designate the marsh tacky horse as the official
3 Georgia heritage horse breed; to provide legislative findings and declarations; to provide for
4 related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 The General Assembly finds and declares as follows:
8 (1) The presence of the marsh tacky horse in Georgia can be traced back to the 1500s;
9 (2) The marsh tacky horse has been used by every culture and class of people that
10 encountered it, including Indigenous nations, like the Seminoles, the Creek, the
11 Chickasaw, the Choctaw, and the Cherokee; European settlers; and the Maroon and
12 Gullah communities;
13 (3) General Francis "Swamp Fox" Marion utilized marsh tacky horses to navigate
14 through rough, swampy terrain during guerilla campaigns against the British;
15 (4) The marsh tacky horse was the predominant stock horse in the southeastern United
16 States up to the 1930s;
