17 (5) During the Great Depression and Dust Bowl eras, larger cattle were brought in from
18 the West requiring larger horses causing the marsh tacky horse to fall out of use;
19 (6) The marsh tacky horse is listed as "critical" under the endangered categories by the
20 Livestock Conservancy;
21 (7) There are less than 2,000 marsh tacky horses in existence;
22 (8) Despite the number of marsh tacky horses remaining, they are still used in hunting
23 wild game and herding cattle; and
24 (9) Establishing the marsh tacky horse as the official Georgia heritage horse breed is
25 necessary to fully recognize the importance of the breed and its contributions to Georgia
26 history.
27 SECTION 2.
28 Article 3 of Chapter 3 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to other
29 state symbols, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
30 "50-3-94.
31 The marsh tacky horse is designated as the official Georgia heritage horse breed."
32 SECTION 3.
33 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
